body:
I'd argue that interface+supported types would be great for introspection and dynamic lookup, but also an overkill for the use case.

The custom delegate type compiles just fine for .NET 2.0, and it's composable and statically verified if one wanted to include multiple formatters, chain-of-responsibility style.
How about something like this...

Given the delegate types:

``` csharp
    public delegate string ValueFormatter(object val);
    public delegate ValueFormatter ValueFormatterFactory(ValueFormatter next);
```

with MsgUtil having an aggregator in MsgUtil:

``` csharp
    static ValueFormatter ValueFormatter = val => string.Format(Fmt_Default, val);
    public static void AddFormatter(ValueFormatterFactory formatterFactory)
    {
        ValueFormatter = formatterFactory(ValueFormatter);
    }
```

one could add any number of formatters to the pipeline, like this:

``` csharp
   MsgUtils.AddFormatter(next => val => (val is String) ? "val" : next(val));
```
